    <h2>2. General Information on Data Processing</h2>
    <p>
        We take the protection of your personal data seriously. We process
        personal data in accordance with the Swiss Data Protection Act
        (DSG, revDSG) and – where applicable – the EU GDPR. We implement
        appropriate technical and organisational measures to protect your
        data against unauthorised access, loss, misuse or alteration.
    </p>
    <p>
        Personal data means any information relating to an identified or
        identifiable natural person. This includes, in particular, master
        data (e.g. name, address), contact details, contract data, order
        data, payment data and online identifiers (e.g. IP address,
        cookie IDs).
    </p>

    <h2>3. Purposes of Data Processing</h2>
    <p>We process your data for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Providing and operating our website and online shop</li>
        <li>Processing orders and fulfilling contracts</li>
        <li>Complying with legal obligations (especially age verification for alcohol sales)</li>
        <li>Communicating with you (e.g. inquiries, support)</li>
        <li>Processing payments</li>
        <li>Sending newsletters (if you have subscribed)</li>
        <li>Analysing and improving our website and services</li>
        <li>Protecting our legitimate interests (e.g. IT security, fraud prevention)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Legal Bases</h2>
    <p>
        We process personal data in accordance with Swiss data protection
        law (DSG, revDSG). Where the EU GDPR applies – in particular when
        offering services to individuals in the EEA – we additionally rely
        on the legal bases set out in Art. 6 GDPR (e.g. contract performance,
        legal obligation, legitimate interests, consent).
    </p>

    <h2>5. Provision of the Website and Server Log Files</h2>
    <p>
        When you access our website, your browser automatically transmits
        information to our server, which is temporarily stored in server
        log files. This may include:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>IP address of the requesting device</li>
        <li>Date and time of access</li>
        <li>Name and URL of the accessed file</li>
        <li>Website from which the access originated (referrer URL)</li>
        <li>Browser type and operating system</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        This data is processed to ensure a stable connection, maintain
        system security and for administrative purposes. It is not used
        to identify you personally.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Registration and Customer Account</h2>
    <p>
        You may create a customer account in our online shop. We process
        the following data in this context:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Salutation, first and last name</li>
        <li>Billing and shipping address</li>
        <li>Email address and password</li>
        <li>Order and transaction history</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        The data is processed to fulfil contracts, manage your customer
        account and simplify future orders.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Orders and Contract Fulfilment</h2>
    <p>
        When you place an order, we process the data you provide, including:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Master data (name, address)</li>
        <li>Contact details (email, phone)</li>
        <li>Order details (products, cart contents, prices)</li>
        <li>Payment information (depending on the payment method)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        Processing is carried out for pre-contractual measures, contract
        fulfilment, compliance with legal obligations (e.g. retention
        requirements) and to protect our legitimate interests (e.g. debt
        collection, fraud prevention).
    </p>

    <h2>8. Age Verification for Alcohol Sales</h2>
    <p>
        When selling alcoholic products, we are legally required to verify
        the minimum age of our customers (e.g. under Swiss food law such as
        Art. 136 LGV). For this purpose, we perform an age verification
        process.
    </p>
    <p>The following data may be processed:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>First and last name</li>
        <li>Date of birth</li>
        <li>Address data</li>
        <li>ID document data (e.g. ID number, issuing country)</li>
        <li>ID image or scan</li>
        <li>Verification result (over 18: yes/no)</li>
        <li>Technical metadata (e.g. session ID, timestamp)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        Age verification may be performed internally or via specialised
        third-party providers (e.g. identity or age verification services).
        These providers process the data on our behalf and according to our
        instructions (data processing agreement).
    </p>
    <p>
        Data is stored only as long as necessary to fulfil the legal
        obligation or document the verification result. ID images are
        deleted after verification unless otherwise required by law.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Payment Service Providers</h2>
    <p>
        To process payments, we use external payment service providers
        (e.g. credit card providers, PayPal, TWINT, instant payment
        services). The data required for payment processing is transmitted
        to these providers.
    </p>
    <p>Processed data may include:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Master data (name, first name)</li>
        <li>Billing and shipping address</li>
        <li>Order amount, currency, transaction number</li>
        <li>Payment information (depending on the method)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        Payment providers process data either as independent controllers
        or as processors. For details, please refer to the privacy policies
        of the respective providers.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Newsletter</h2>
    <p>
        If you subscribe to our newsletter, we use your email address and,
        if provided, your name to send you regular updates about our
        products and offers. Subscription typically uses a double opt-in
        process.
    </p>
    <p>
        We may use an external email marketing service provider to send
        newsletters. This provider processes your data on our behalf and
        according to our instructions. Processing is based on your consent
        or – where applicable – Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR.
    </p>
    <p>
        You may withdraw your consent at any time with future effect by
        using the unsubscribe link in the newsletter or by contacting us.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Cookies and Similar Technologies</h2>
    <p>
        We use cookies and similar technologies to provide essential
        website functions, analyse usage and improve our services.
    </p>
    <p>
        Cookies are small text files stored on your device. Some cookies
        are technically necessary (e.g. session cookies, cart cookies),
        while others serve analytical or marketing purposes.
    </p>
    <p>
        You can configure your browser to block or delete cookies. If you
        disable cookies, some website functions may be limited.
    </p>
    <p>
        Where required, we obtain your consent for analytics or marketing
        cookies and inform you via our cookie banner or cookie settings.
    </p>

    <h2>12. Web Analytics and Tracking</h2>
    <p>
        We may use web analytics tools (e.g. Google Analytics or similar)
        to analyse website usage and improve our services. These tools may
        set cookies and transmit usage data to the provider’s servers.
    </p>
    <p>Processed data may include:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>IP address (possibly truncated)</li>
        <li>Date and time of visit</li>
        <li>Pages viewed and content accessed</li>
        <li>Browser type and operating system</li>
        <li>Referrer URL</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        Where required, such tools are only used with your consent. You may
        withdraw your consent at any time via the cookie settings.
    </p>

    <h2>13. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>
        We may integrate third-party content and services on our website,
        such as:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Maps (e.g. Google Maps)</li>
        <li>Fonts (e.g. Google Fonts)</li>
        <li>Videos (e.g. YouTube)</li>
        <li>Security services (e.g. reCAPTCHA)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        When using these services, data (especially IP address and usage
        data) may be transmitted to the provider’s servers. If data is
        transferred to countries without adequate data protection (e.g.
        the USA), this is based on appropriate safeguards (e.g. Standard
        Contractual Clauses) and additional security measures.
    </p>

    <h2>14. Data Transfers Abroad</h2>
    <p>
        Data may be transferred abroad, particularly when using third-party
        services (e.g. hosting, newsletter, analytics, payment providers,
        age verification services).
    </p>
    <p>We ensure adequate data protection through:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Adequacy decisions by competent authorities</li>
        <li>Standard Contractual Clauses (SCC)</li>
        <li>Technical and organisational security measures</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>15. Storage Period</h2>
    <p>
        We store personal data only as long as necessary for the respective
        purpose or as required by law. After the purpose ceases or retention
        periods expire, data is deleted or anonymised.
    </p>

    <h2>16. Data Security</h2>
    <p>
        We implement appropriate technical and organisational measures
        (TOMs) to protect your data against loss, misuse, unauthorised
        access, alteration or destruction. These include access controls,
        encryption, backup concepts and regular reviews of our security
        measures.
    </p>

    <h2>17. Rights of Data Subjects</h2>
    <p>
        Under Swiss data protection law (DSG, revDSG), you have the
        following rights:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Right of access to your personal data</li>
        <li>Right to rectification of inaccurate or incomplete data</li>
        <li>Right to deletion of personal data (unless legal obligations prevent this)</li>
        <li>Right to restrict processing</li>
        <li>Right to receive or transfer certain data</li>
        <li>Right to object to certain processing activities</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        Where the GDPR applies, additional rights may exist (e.g. data
        portability, right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory
        authority).
    </p>
    <p>
        To exercise your rights, please contact us using the details
        provided in Section 1. We may request proof of identity to protect
        your data.
    </p>

    <h2>18. Contact for Data Protection Matters</h2>
    <p>
        For questions regarding data protection or to exercise your rights,
        please contact:
    </p>
    <p>
        [Data Protection Contact / same as Controller]<br>
        Email: [Data Protection Email Address]
    </p>

    <h2>19. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>
        We may update this privacy policy at any time. The version published
        on our website applies. Significant changes will be communicated in
        an appropriate manner.
    </p>
